<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Eric Plante</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Ok, now I am confuse and angry at Verant to have given us such a bad rule book!<P>I was told by a GM and confirm by the player's handbook, that DEX only affect missile attacks and spell casting but I always hear Monks saying that having a high DEX make a difference in battle so, what else does it affect?<P>I've heard that it helps getting max dmg more often and that it helps Dual Wield and Double Attack but it seems to be pure speculation, not true knowledge.<P>I want facts from experimentation or true knowledge, not opinions. I hope Verant will put a better rule book in the expension!<P>Thanks</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Gruntz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I was told a long way back by a GM that dex was broken...however I can guarantee that if you have a weapon with an effect (ghoulbane....stilletto of bloodclaw etc.) the effect WILL go off more with high Dex.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">DARK</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">IM A LVL 19 monk and when im buffed my dex is <BR>120 unbuffed and with no dex rings braclets ect on im 80. what i have found is when im 80 i normaly hit 1-2 per turn mostly a few 3 for 15 damage max. now when im buffed with dex at 120 i hit 2-3 per turn mostly with the same 15 damage(also misses seem to drop with more dex)<P>i tested this because i wanted to see if i should go for agi or dex mosty.<P>hope this helps <BR>dark</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Asura Threndor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Ok im a lvl 26 ranger and i have also expirimented with dex.  Me and a rouge of the same skill at 2x weild and 2x attack squared off with a dragoon dirk in our main hand. He had more dex then me and the rest of our skill where similar. He attacked faster then i did every time.  So in my opinion dex determines how fast you attack</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">PhantomNA</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Dexterity is nothing more than your chances of doing something a certain amount of times.<P>The more dexterous you are, the better you are at something, and the more you'll do it.<P>More dexterity means more double attacks, more dual wield hits, more dmg caused by your weapon, less misses, more chances of your item/weapon going off, etc etc.  In battle AGI and DEX work inversely: DEX lets you hit your target more, and harder, while AGI lets your target miss you more, and cause less dmg.<P>When you work on your game, basketball for example, you'll get better and better, you'll make more and more shots than before you practiced so much, because you're getting more dexterous with your hands and with your coordination.  Same thing in eq.<P>Hope that helps.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</FONT>
